  <summary date="2009-10-09T17:05:36Z" status="Introduced in House">Amends Rule XXI (Restrictions on Certain Bills) of the Rules of the House of Representatives to make it out of order to consider a rule or order that waives the application of the Pay-As-You-Go (PAYGO) rule in the House.

Prescribes a procedure for disposing of a related point of order.

Makes it out of order for the Speaker to entertain a motion to suspend application of the PAYGO rule.</summary>
